  "text": "When the antenna shown in Fig. 10 is in service, we let all the loaded PIN diodes present capacitance characteristics by applying a reverse DC bias voltage across each diode in order to maintain optimal radiation performances. During the process of simulation, we take 0.15 pF as the typical value of both C eq1 and C eq2 [CITATION_1] . Although two cascaded diodes are used to decrease the total cascaded capacitance, there is a resonant frequency shift occurs. In order to compare antenna performances at the same operating frequency, L is only decreased by 2.7 mm to ensure the antenna shown in Fig. 10 operates at 2.5 GHz.",
